  "prompt": "How much did it cost to build Walt Disney World?",
  "response": "The cost to build Walt Disney World in Florida was substantial, especially considering the scale and ambition of the project. When Walt Disney World Resort first opened in 1971, the initial construction cost was around **$400 million** (approximately **$2.8 billion** in today's dollars). This included the Magic Kingdom theme park, resorts, infrastructure, and transportation systems.\n\nOver the years, the resort has expanded significantly with the addition of EPCOT, Disney's Hollywood Studios, Disney's Animal Kingdom, water parks, numerous hotels, shopping districts (like Disney Springs), and other amenities. The total investment in the resort to date is estimated to be in the **tens of billions of dollars**.\n\nFor comparison:\n- **Magic Kingdom (1971)**: $400 million at the time.\n- **EPCOT (1982)**: Approximately $1.4 billion.\n- **Disney's Hollywood Studios (1989)**: Around $500 million.\n- **Disney's Animal Kingdom (1998)**: Approximately $800 million.\n\nThese figures don't account for ongoing maintenance, upgrades, and new attractions added over the decades. Disney continues to invest heavily in Walt Disney World, making it one of the most expensive and complex entertainment destinations in the world.",
